node.text:
Coastal walks can be hard to beat, especially on a day like this. A wander atop the cliffs, and back around past some beautiful trees and plants that I just don't see up in Edinburgh's colder climes... I love this time of year, with the swathes of yellow popping from the gorse bushes.

It also gave me the opportunity to try out my new kicks, a lovely spring/summer pair of the @merrelleu Moab Speed 2.

One of the things I love about my Merrells is that I've never had to beak a pair in; they are comfy and bouncy from the off, and I don't think twice about heading out for a long walk the first time I wear them.
Lovely part of the world, especially when the sun shines…funny I’ve never had to beak-in a pair of Merrells either!! 😂❤️
Looks lush Nicky and the Merrelle looks good🥾🌊
Beautyful... I walked the Coast Path near Paignton over 10 years ago. It was so great.👏
Gorgeous pictures Nicky, you’re so lucky to be staying in the sunniest, most beautiful county in the World!! ☀️☀️🔥😍
Stunning! Hard to believe you're in the UK. And I definitely want to go on holiday now!
Both nature and people are obvious pretty in Scotland 😍
Love the coast, though needs rocky cliffs and sandy beaches! North West has the beaches but not enough of the cliffs 😍
I love that area and visit many times a year just to walk that stretch of coastline
Looks so gorgeous 😍 definitely adding to my must visit list! Xx
You came down on a beautiful weekend ☀️ !  it is a lovely walk all alone that coastal path
Visit Cove Harbour, not too far from Edinburgh, a hidden gem. 💎
